parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the engine to run poorly, leading to decreased performance, reduced fuel efficiency, and increased emissions, which can harm the environment and pose a risk to public health.
symptoms: The engine runs rough or misfires
the vehicle experiences a loss of power
the vehicle's fuel efficiency decreases
the "check engine" light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle emits excessive exhaust smoke or odor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, and can result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies
the engine makes unusual noises or vibrations
the engine overheats
the engine oil or coolant levels drop
the "check engine" light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
the engine stalls while driving
the ignition switch feels loose or worn out
the key gets stuck in the ignition
the dashboard warning lights illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle to stall or run poorly, leading to reduced engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle's "check engine" light illuminates
the engine stalls or hesitates
the engine runs rough or misfires
the vehicle's performance is sluggish
the fuel economy is poor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ride control system can cause the vehicle to experience uneven ride quality, reduced handling, and decreased stability, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle exhibits uneven ride quality
bounces excessively
or leans excessively to one side while driving
the vehicle's suspension makes unusual noises
the vehicle's ride height is lower than normal
the vehicle's shocks or struts are leaking fluid.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can lead to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of brake pedal
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal travels to the floor
difficulty stopping the vehicle
grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes
warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes stiff or hard to turn
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the power steering fluid level is low
the power steering pump is noisy or whining
the vehicle is difficult to steer
especially when driving at low speeds.
